The function checking whether a given string is a palindrome is in the
server/routes/palindrome.js
file.

To run the mongo daemon, use the following command:
mongod --dbpath ./db --port 27018

To run the server, first cd into the server folder and run npm install.
Then use:
node server

To run the client app, cd into client and run npm install here, too.
Then you can use:
npm start
or
ng serve --o
to automatically open the browser window.
